The paper deals with privacy-preserving algorithms and information theory, which are common topics in the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of clustering algorithms also suggests a possible fit in the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
